    "description": "The strategy is a monthly equity selection model that targets stocks exhibiting positive idiosyncratic performance relative to the broad US market. It estimates each Dow 30 constituent’s short term alpha versus SPY by running a 21 trading day linear regression of the stock’s daily returns on SPY’s daily returns, using the regression intercept as the alpha proxy. The intended edge is to capture persistent security specific strength not explained by market beta, effectively rotating into Dow names with the strongest recent market adjusted drift.\n\nThe investable universe is the constituents of the DIA ETF (Dow 30), with SPY used solely as the benchmark factor. Decisions are made at the start of each month using daily close data from the prior 21 sessions. The portfolio is rebalanced into the top two names by estimated alpha, equally weighted at 50 percent each, and fully exits names that fall out of the top two at the next rebalance. The strategy is always fully invested and does not apply volatility targeting, leverage limits beyond 100 percent gross exposure, stop losses, or explicit drawdown controls; risk is primarily driven by concentrated two stock exposure and turnover at the monthly rebalance.",
